xIsisSysTable.name: xIsisSysTable
xIsisSysTable.description: The set of instances of the Integrated IS-IS protocol existing on the system.

xIsisSysEntry.name: xIsisSysEntry
xIsisSysEntry.description: Each row defines information specific to a single instance of the protocol existing on the system.

xIsisSysInstance.name: xIsisSysInstance
xIsisSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

xIsisSysExistState.name: xIsisSysExistState
xIsisSysExistState.description: The validity of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This object follows the existenceState behaviour.

xIsisSysVersion.name: xIsisSysVersion
xIsisSysVersion.description: The version number of the IS-IS protocol to which this instance conforms. This value must be set by the implementation when the row is valid.

xIsisSysType.name: xIsisSysType
xIsisSysType.description: The type of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

xIsisSysNET.name: xIsisSysNET
xIsisSysNET.description: The ID for this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. This value is appended to each of the instance's area addresses to form the Network Entity Titles valid for this instance. The derivation of a value for this object is implementation-specific. Some implementations may assign values and not permit write access, others may require the value to be set manually.

xIsisSysMaxPathSplits.name: xIsisSysMaxPathSplits
xIsisSysMaxPathSplits.description: Maximum number of paths with equal routing metric value which it is permitted to split between. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

xIsisSysMinLSPTransInt.name: xIsisSysMinLSPTransInt
xIsisSysMinLSPTransInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between re-transmission of an LSP. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

xIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt.name: xIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt
xIsisSysMaxLSPGenInt.description: Maximum interval, in seconds, between generated LSPs by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

xIsisSysMinBroadLSPTransInt.name: xIsisSysMinBroadLSPTransInt
xIsisSysMinBroadLSPTransInt.description: Minimum interval, in milliseconds, between transmission of LSPs on a broadcast circuit. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour. This timer shall be capable of a resolution not coarser than 10 milliseconds.

xIsisSysCompSNPInt.name: xIsisSysCompSNPInt
xIsisSysCompSNPInt.description: Interval, in seconds, between generation of Complete Sequence Numbers PDUs by a designated Intermediate System on a broadcast circuit. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

xIsisSysOrigL1LSPBuffSize.name: xIsisSysOrigL1LSPBuffSize
xIsisSysOrigL1LSPBuffSize.description: The maximum size of Level 1 LSPs and SNPs originated by this instance. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

xIsisSysMaxAreaAddr.name: xIsisSysMaxAreaAddr
xIsisSysMaxAreaAddr.description: The maximum number of area addresses to be permitted for the area in which this instance exists. Note that all Intermediate Systems in the same area must have the same value configured for this attribute if correct operation is to be assumed. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

xIsisSysMinLSPGenInt.name: xIsisSysMinLSPGenInt
xIsisSysMinLSPGenInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between successive generation of LSPs with the same LSPID by this instance. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

xIsisSysPollESHelloRate.name: xIsisSysPollESHelloRate
xIsisSysPollESHelloRate.description: The value, in seconds, to be used for the suggested ES configuration timer in ISH PDUs when soliciting the ES configuration.

xIsisSysPartSNPInt.name: xIsisSysPartSNPInt
xIsisSysPartSNPInt.description: Minimum interval between sending Partial Sequence Number PDUs. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

xIsisSysWaitTime.name: xIsisSysWaitTime
xIsisSysWaitTime.description: Number of seconds to delay in waiting state before entering on state. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

xIsisSysDRISISHelloTimer.name: xIsisSysDRISISHelloTimer
xIsisSysDRISISHelloTimer.description: The interval, in seconds, between the generation of IIH PDUs by the designated IS on a LAN. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

xIsisSysOperState.name: xIsisSysOperState
xIsisSysOperState.description: The operational state of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol. Setting this object to the value on when its current value is off enables operation of this instance of the Integrated IS-IS protocol.

xIsisSysL1State.name: xIsisSysL1State
xIsisSysL1State.description: The state of the Level 1 database.

xIsisSysL1LSPDbaseOloads.name: xIsisSysL1LSPDbaseOloads
xIsisSysL1LSPDbaseOloads.description: Number of times the LSP L1 database has become overloaded.

xIsisSysManAddrsDropFromArea.name: xIsisSysManAddrsDropFromArea
xIsisSysManAddrsDropFromArea.description: Number of times a manual address has been dropped from the area.

xIsisSysAttmptsToExMaxSeqNum.name: xIsisSysAttmptsToExMaxSeqNum
xIsisSysAttmptsToExMaxSeqNum.description: Number of times the IS has attempted to exceed the maximum sequence number.

xIsisSysSeqNumSkips.name: xIsisSysSeqNumSkips
xIsisSysSeqNumSkips.description: Number of times a sequence number skip has occurred.

xIsisSysOwnLSPPurges.name: xIsisSysOwnLSPPurges
xIsisSysOwnLSPPurges.description: Number of times a zero-aged copy of the system's own LSP is received from some other node.

xIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches.name: xIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches
xIsisSysIDFieldLenMismatches.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for ID field length to that of the receiving system.

xIsisSysMaxAreaMis.name: xIsisSysMaxAreaMis
xIsisSysMaxAreaMis.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for MaximumAreaAddresses from that of the receiving system.

xIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize.name: xIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize
xIsisSysOrigL2LSPBuffSize.description: The maximum size of Level 2 LSPs and SNPs originated by this system. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

xIsisSysL2State.name: xIsisSysL2State
xIsisSysL2State.description: The state of the Level 2 database.

xIsisSysL2LSPDbaseOloads.name: xIsisSysL2LSPDbaseOloads
xIsisSysL2LSPDbaseOloads.description: Number of times the Level 2 LSP database has become overloaded.

xIsisSysMaxAreaCheck.name: xIsisSysMaxAreaCheck
xIsisSysMaxAreaCheck.description: When on, enables checking of maximum area addresses per IS version of ISO10589.

xIsisManAreaAddrTable.name: xIsisManAreaAddrTable
xIsisManAreaAddrTable.description: The set of manual area addresses configured on this Intermediate System.

xIsisManAreaAddrEntry.name: xIsisManAreaAddrEntry
xIsisManAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address manually configured on this system

xIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance.name: xIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance
xIsisManAreaAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

xIsisManAreaAddr.name: xIsisManAreaAddr
xIsisManAreaAddr.description: A manually configured area address for this system. This object follows the index behaviour.

xIsisManAreaAddrExistState.name: xIsisManAreaAddrExistState
xIsisManAreaAddrExistState.description: The state of the xIsisManAreaAddrEntry. This object follows the ExistenceState behaviour. If an attempt is made to set this object to the value off when the corresponding xIsisManAreaAddrEntry is the only valid entry for this instance and when the corresponding ISIS instance has xIsisSysOperState set to On then the attempt is rejected.

xIsisAreaAddrTable.name: xIsisAreaAddrTable
xIsisAreaAddrTable.description: The union of the sets of area addresses reported in all Level 1 LSPs received by this instance of the protocol.

xIsisAreaAddrEntry.name: xIsisAreaAddrEntry
xIsisAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address reported in a Level 1 LSP received by this instance of the protocol.

xIsisAreaAddrSysInstance.name: xIsisAreaAddrSysInstance
xIsisAreaAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds.

xIsisAreaAddr.name: xIsisAreaAddr
xIsisAreaAddr.description: An area address reported in a Level 1 LSP received by this instance of the protocol.

xIsisSysProtSuppTable.name: xIsisSysProtSuppTable
xIsisSysProtSuppTable.description: This table contains the manually configured set of protocols supported by each instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

xIsisSysProtSuppEntry.name: xIsisSysProtSuppEntry
xIsisSysProtSuppEntry.description: Each entry contains one protocol supported by an instance of the Integrated ISIS protocol.

xIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance.name: xIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance
xIsisSysProtSuppSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

xIsisSysProtSuppProtocol.name: xIsisSysProtSuppProtocol
xIsisSysProtSuppProtocol.description: One supported protocol. This object follows the index behaviour.

xIsisSysProtSuppExistState.name: xIsisSysProtSuppExistState
xIsisSysProtSuppExistState.description: The state of the xIsisSysProtSuppEntry. This object follows the ExistenceState and ReplaceOnlyWhileInstanceDisabled behaviours.

xIsisCircTable.name: xIsisCircTable
xIsisCircTable.description: The table of circuits used by each instance of Integrated IS-IS on this system.

xIsisCircEntry.name: xIsisCircEntry
xIsisCircEntry.description: An xIsisCircEntry exists for each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

xIsisCircSysInstance.name: xIsisCircSysInstance
xIsisCircSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index behaviour.

xIsisCircIndex.name: xIsisCircIndex
xIsisCircIndex.description: The identifier of this circuit, unique within the instance of the protocol. This object follows the index behaviour.

xIsisCircIfIndex.name: xIsisCircIfIndex
xIsisCircIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface to which this circuit corresponds. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

xIsisCircOperState.name: xIsisCircOperState
xIsisCircOperState.description: The operational state of the circuit. This object follows the operationalState behaviour.

xIsisCircExistState.name: xIsisCircExistState
xIsisCircExistState.description: The existence state of this circuit. This object follows the ExistenceState behaviour.

xIsisCircType.name: xIsisCircType
xIsisCircType.description: The type of the circuit. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour. The type specified must be compatible with the type of the interface defined by the value of xIsisCircIfIndex.

xIsisCircHelloTimer.name: xIsisCircHelloTimer
xIsisCircHelloTimer.description: The period, in seconds, between IIH PDUs. It is also used as the period between ISH PDUs when polling the ES configuration. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

xIsisCircL1DefaultMetric.name: xIsisCircL1DefaultMetric
xIsisCircL1DefaultMetric.description: The default metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. 0 means the IS will automatically generate Level 1 default metric for the circuit.

xIsisCircL1DelayMetric.name: xIsisCircL1DelayMetric
xIsisCircL1DelayMetric.description: The delay metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

xIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric.name: xIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric
xIsisCircL1ExpenseMetric.description: The expense metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

xIsisCircL1ErrorMetric.name: xIsisCircL1ErrorMetric
xIsisCircL1ErrorMetric.description: The error metric value of this circuit for Level 1 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

xIsisCircExtDomain.name: xIsisCircExtDomain
xIsisCircExtDomain.description: If true, suppress normal transmission of and interpretation of Intra-domain ISIS PDUs on this circuit.

xIsisCircAdjChanges.name: xIsisCircAdjChanges
xIsisCircAdjChanges.description: The number of times an adjacency state change has occurred on this circuit.

xIsisCircInitFails.name: xIsisCircInitFails
xIsisCircInitFails.description: The number of times initialization of this circuit has failed.

xIsisCircRejAdjs.name: xIsisCircRejAdjs
xIsisCircRejAdjs.description: The number of times an adjacency has been rejected on this circuit.

xIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs.name: xIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs
xIsisCircOutCtrlPDUs.description: The number of IS-IS control PDUs sent on this circuit.

xIsisCircInCtrlPDUs.name: xIsisCircInCtrlPDUs
xIsisCircInCtrlPDUs.description: The number of IS-IS control PDUs received on this circuit.

xIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches.name: xIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches
xIsisCircIDFieldLenMismatches.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with an ID field length different to that for this system has been received.

xIsisCircL2DefaultMetric.name: xIsisCircL2DefaultMetric
xIsisCircL2DefaultMetric.description: The default metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. 0 means the IS will automatically generate the Level 2 default metric for this circuit.

xIsisCircL2DelayMetric.name: xIsisCircL2DelayMetric
xIsisCircL2DelayMetric.description: The delay metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

xIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric.name: xIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric
xIsisCircL2ExpenseMetric.description: The expense metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

xIsisCircL2ErrorMetric.name: xIsisCircL2ErrorMetric
xIsisCircL2ErrorMetric.description: The error metric value of this circuit for level 2 traffic. The value of zero is reserved to indicate that this metric is not supported.

xIsisCircManL2Only.name: xIsisCircManL2Only
xIsisCircManL2Only.description: When true, indicates that this circuit is to be used only for level 2. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behaviour.

xIsisCircL1ISPriority.name: xIsisCircL1ISPriority
xIsisCircL1ISPriority.description: The priority for becoming LAN Level 1 Deignated Intermediate System on a broadcast circuit.

xIsisCircL1CircID.name: xIsisCircL1CircID
xIsisCircL1CircID.description: The LAN ID allocated by the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System. Where this system is not aware of the value (because it is not participating in the Level 1 Designated Intermediate System election), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one octet local Circuit ID for this circuit.

xIsisCircL1DesIS.name: xIsisCircL1DesIS
xIsisCircL1DesIS.description: The ID of the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System on this circuit. If, for any reason this system is not partaking in the relevant Designated Intermediate System election process, then the value returned is the zero length OCTET STRING.

xIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges.name: xIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges
xIsisCircLANL1DesISChanges.description: The number of times the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System has changed.

xIsisCircL2ISPriority.name: xIsisCircL2ISPriority
xIsisCircL2ISPriority.description: The priority for becoming LAN level 2 Designated Intermediate System.

xIsisCircL2CircID.name: xIsisCircL2CircID
xIsisCircL2CircID.description: The LAN ID allocated by the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System. Where this system is not aware of this value (because it is not participating in the Level 2 Designated Intermediate System election), this object has the value which would be proposed for this circuit (i.e. the concatenation of the local system ID and the one octet local Circuit ID for this circuit.

xIsisCircL2DesIS.name: xIsisCircL2DesIS
xIsisCircL2DesIS.description: The ID of the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System on this circuit. If, for any reason, this system is not partaking in the relevant Designated Intermediate System election process, then the value returned is the zero length OCTET STRING.

xIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges.name: xIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges
xIsisCircLANL2DesISChanges.description: The number of times the LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System has changed.

xIsisCircISTable.name: xIsisCircISTable
xIsisCircISTable.description: The set of objects controlling the operation of the IS functions of the ES-IS protocol (ISO 9542) on each circuit over which ISIS is run.

xIsisCircISEntry.name: xIsisCircISEntry
xIsisCircISEntry.description: Each entry contains objects controlling the operation of the IS functions of the ES-IS protocol (ISO 9542) on one circuit.

xIsisCircISSysInstance.name: xIsisCircISSysInstance
xIsisCircISSysInstance.description: The identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

xIsisCircISIndex.name: xIsisCircISIndex
xIsisCircISIndex.description: The unique identifier of this row. This value is the same as the value of the ifIndex object which identifies the interface which corresponds to this circuit. This object follows the index behaviour.

xIsisCircISExistState.name: xIsisCircISExistState
xIsisCircISExistState.description: The existence state of this row. This object follows the ExistenceState behaviour.

xIsisCircISOperState.name: xIsisCircISOperState
xIsisCircISOperState.description: The operational state of the row. This object follows the operationalState behaviour.

xIsisCircISHoldTimerMult.name: xIsisCircISHoldTimerMult
xIsisCircISHoldTimerMult.description: The factor to derive holding timer from configuration timer. This value when multipled by a configuration timer yields the value of the holding timer parameter issued with configuration information. The semantics of this parameter are such that it is permissible to add a delta value to the result to compensate for possible delays and imprecision of timers. The result of the calculation is truncated, upon overflow, to the maximum value for the parameter permitted by the protocol (65535).

xIsisCircISConfTimer.name: xIsisCircISConfTimer
xIsisCircISConfTimer.description: Value in seconds for the ISO 9542 IS configuration timer. It is used to determine how often an IS reports configuration information to ESs. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

xIsisCircISSuggESConfTimer.name: xIsisCircISSuggESConfTimer
xIsisCircISSuggESConfTimer.description: Value to be used for the ISO 9542 suggested ES configuration timer value (in seconds), advertised in IS Hellos generated by the system on this circuit. This object follows the resettingTimer behaviour.

xIsisCircISRedHoldTime.name: xIsisCircISRedHoldTime
xIsisCircISRedHoldTime.description: The holding time (in seconds) to be specified in Redirect PDUs generated by the system on this circuit.

xIsisCircISESReachChgs.name: xIsisCircISESReachChgs
xIsisCircISESReachChgs.description: Count of the number of changes in reachability of End Systems from this circuit.

xIsisCircISInv9542PDUs.name: xIsisCircISInv9542PDUs
xIsisCircISInv9542PDUs.description: Counter of invalid 9542 PDUs received. This is the number of ISO 9452 PDUs received which are discarded as a result of the PDU Header Error Detection or Protocol Error Processing Functions specified in ISO 9542.

xIsisISAdjTable.name: xIsisISAdjTable
xIsisISAdjTable.description: The table of adjacencies to Intermediate Systems.

xIsisISAdjEntry.name: xIsisISAdjEntry
xIsisISAdjEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one adjacency to an Intermediate System on this system.

xIsisISAdjSysInstance.name: xIsisISAdjSysInstance
xIsisISAdjSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds.

xIsisISAdjCircIndex.name: xIsisISAdjCircIndex
xIsisISAdjCircIndex.description: The identifier of the Circuit which is the parent of the IS adjacency.

xIsisISAdjIndex.name: xIsisISAdjIndex
xIsisISAdjIndex.description: A unique value identifying the IS adjacency from all other such adjacencies on this circuit. This value is assigned by the system when the adjacency is created automatically.

xIsisISAdjNeighSNPAAddress.name: xIsisISAdjNeighSNPAAddress
xIsisISAdjNeighSNPAAddress.description: The SNPA address of the neighboring system.

xIsisISAdjNeighSysType.name: xIsisISAdjNeighSysType
xIsisISAdjNeighSysType.description: The type of the neighboring system.

xIsisISAdjNeighSysID.name: xIsisISAdjNeighSysID
xIsisISAdjNeighSysID.description: The system ID of the neighboring Intermediate System set from the source ID field of the neighbor's IIH PDUs.

xIsisISAdjUsage.name: xIsisISAdjUsage
xIsisISAdjUsage.description: The usage of the adjacency. An adjacency of type level1 will be used for level 1 traffic only. An adjacency of type level2 will be used for level 2 traffic only. An adjacency of type level1and2 will be used for both level 1 and level 2 traffic. There may be two adjacencies (of types level1 and level2) between the same pair of Intermediate Systems.

xIsisISAdjHoldTimer.name: xIsisISAdjHoldTimer
xIsisISAdjHoldTimer.description: The holding time for this adjacency updated from received IIH PDUs.

xIsisISAdjNeighPriority.name: xIsisISAdjNeighPriority
xIsisISAdjNeighPriority.description: Priority of the neighboring Intermediate System for becoming the LAN Level 1 Designated Intermediate System if the value of xIsisISAdjNeighSysType is L1IntermediateSystem or LAN Level 2 Designated Intermediate System if the value of xIsisISAdjNeighSysType is L2IntermediateSystem.

xIsisISAdjAreaAddrTable.name: xIsisISAdjAreaAddrTable
xIsisISAdjAreaAddrTable.description: This table contains the set of Area Addresses of neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

xIsisISAdjAreaAddrEntry.name: xIsisISAdjAreaAddrEntry
xIsisISAdjAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one Area Address reported by a neighboring Intermediate System in its IIH PDUs.

xIsisISAdjAreaAddrSysInstance.name: xIsisISAdjAreaAddrSysInstance
xIsisISAdjAreaAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds.

xIsisISAdjAreaAddrCircIndex.name: xIsisISAdjAreaAddrCircIndex
xIsisISAdjAreaAddrCircIndex.description: The identifier of the Circuit which is the parent of the IS adjacency to which this Area Address entry corresponds.

xIsisISAdjAreaAddrAdjIndex.name: xIsisISAdjAreaAddrAdjIndex
xIsisISAdjAreaAddrAdjIndex.description: The identifier of the IS adjacency to which this entry belongs.

xIsisISAdjAreaAddress.name: xIsisISAdjAreaAddress
xIsisISAdjAreaAddress.description: One Area Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

xIsisISAdjIPAddrTable.name: xIsisISAdjIPAddrTable
xIsisISAdjIPAddrTable.description: This table contains the set of IP Addresses of neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

xIsisISAdjIPAddrEntry.name: xIsisISAdjIPAddrEntry
xIsisISAdjIPAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP Address reported by a neighboring Intermediate System in its IIH PDUs.

xIsisISAdjIPAddrSysInstance.name: xIsisISAdjIPAddrSysInstance
xIsisISAdjIPAddrSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds.

xIsisISAdjIPAddrCircIndex.name: xIsisISAdjIPAddrCircIndex
xIsisISAdjIPAddrCircIndex.description: The identifier of the Circuit which is the parent of the IS adjacency to which this IP Address entry corresponds.

xIsisISAdjIPAddrAdjIndex.name: xIsisISAdjIPAddrAdjIndex
xIsisISAdjIPAddrAdjIndex.description: The identifier of the IS adjacency to which this entry belongs.

xIsisISAdjIPAddress.name: xIsisISAdjIPAddress
xIsisISAdjIPAddress.description: One IP Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

xIsisISAdjProtSuppTable.name: xIsisISAdjProtSuppTable
xIsisISAdjProtSuppTable.description: This table contains the set of protocols supported by neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

xIsisISAdjProtSuppEntry.name: xIsisISAdjProtSuppEntry
xIsisISAdjProtSuppEntry.description: Each entry contains one protocol supported by a neighboring Intermediate System as reported in its IIH PDUs.

xIsisISAdjProtSuppSysInstance.name: xIsisISAdjProtSuppSysInstance
xIsisISAdjProtSuppSysInstance.description: The unique identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds.

xIsisISAdjProtSuppCircIndex.name: xIsisISAdjProtSuppCircIndex
xIsisISAdjProtSuppCircIndex.description: The identifier of the Circuit which is the parent of the IS adjacency to which this supported protocol entry corresponds.

xIsisISAdjProtSuppAdjIndex.name: xIsisISAdjProtSuppAdjIndex
xIsisISAdjProtSuppAdjIndex.description: The identifier the IS adjacency to which this entry corresponds.

xIsisISAdjProtSuppProtocol.name: xIsisISAdjProtSuppProtocol
xIsisISAdjProtSuppProtocol.description: One supported protocol as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

xIsisESAdjTable.name: xIsisESAdjTable
xIsisESAdjTable.description: The table of End System IDs of neighboring End Systems as reported in their ESH PDUs or as configured manually

xIsisESAdjEntry.name: xIsisESAdjEntry
xIsisESAdjEntry.description: Each entry contains one End System ID of a neighboring End System as reported in an ESH PDU or as configured manually.

xIsisESAdjSysInstance.name: xIsisESAdjSysInstance
xIsisESAdjSysInstance.description: The identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

xIsisESAdjCircIndex.name: xIsisESAdjCircIndex
xIsisESAdjCircIndex.description: The identifier of the Circuit which is the parent of the ES adjacency to which this End System ID entry corresponds. This object follows the index and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

xIsisESAdjIndex.name: xIsisESAdjIndex
xIsisESAdjIndex.description: The identifier of the ES adjacency to which this entry belongs. This object follows the index and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

xIsisESAdjType.name: xIsisESAdjType
xIsisESAdjType.description: The indication of whether this adjacency was created manually by management action or automatically by the implementation.

xIsisESAdjState.name: xIsisESAdjState
xIsisESAdjState.description: The state of the adjacency. Adjacencies created manually always have this value set to up.

xIsisESAdjNeighSNPAAddress.name: xIsisESAdjNeighSNPAAddress
xIsisESAdjNeighSNPAAddress.description: The SNPA address of the neighboring system. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

xIsisESAdjExistState.name: xIsisESAdjExistState
xIsisESAdjExistState.description: The existence state of this ES Adjacency. This object follows the ExistenceState behaviour. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

xIsisESAdjESID.name: xIsisESAdjESID
xIsisESAdjESID.description: An End System ID of a neighboring End System. This object follows the index and manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

xIsisRATable.name: xIsisRATable
xIsisRATable.description: The table of Reachable Addresses to NSAPs or Address Prefixes.

xIsisRAEntry.name: xIsisRAEntry
xIsisRAEntry.description: Each entry defines a Reachable Address to a NSAP or Address Prefix.

xIsisRASysInstance.name: xIsisRASysInstance
xIsisRASysInstance.description: The identifier of the Integrated IS-IS instance to which this row corresponds. This object follows the index and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

xIsisRACircIndex.name: xIsisRACircIndex
xIsisRACircIndex.description: The identifier of the Circuit over which this destination is reachable. This object follows the index and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

xIsisRAIndex.name: xIsisRAIndex
xIsisRAIndex.description: The identifier for this xIsisRAEntry. This value must be unique amongst all Reachable Addresses on the same parent Circuit. This object follows the index and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

xIsisRAExistState.name: xIsisRAExistState
xIsisRAExistState.description: The existence state of this Reachable Address. This object follows the ExistenceState and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

xIsisRAOperState.name: xIsisRAOperState
xIsisRAOperState.description: The operational state of the Reachable Address. This object follows the operationalState and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

xIsisRAAddrPrefix.name: xIsisRAAddrPrefix
xIsisRAAddrPrefix.description: The destination of this Reachable Address. This is an Address Prefix. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled and manualOrAutomatic behaviours.

xIsisRAMapType.name: xIsisRAMapType
xIsisRAMapType.description: The type of mapping to be employed to ascertain the SNPA Address which should be used in forwarding PDUs for this Reachable Address prefix. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour. The following values of mapping type are defined: none: The mapping is null because the neighbor SNPA is implicit by nature of the subnetwork (e.g. a point-to-point linkage). explicit: The subnetwork addresses in the object xIsisRASNPAAddress is to be used. extractIDI: The SNPA is embedded in the IDI of the destination NSAP Address. The mapping algorithm extracts the SNPA to be used according to the format and encoding rules of ISO8473/Add2. This SNPA extraction algorithm can be used in conjunction with Reachable Address prefixes from the X.121, F.69, E.163 and E.164 addressing subdomains. extractDSP: All, or a suffix, of the SNPA is embedded in the DSP of the destination address. This SNPA extraction algorithm extracts the embedded subnetwork addressing information by performing a logical AND of the xIsisRASNPAMask object value with the destination address. The part of the SNPA extracted from the destination NSAP is appended to the xIsisRASNPAPrefix object value to form the next hop subnetwork addressing information.

xIsisRADelMetric.name: xIsisRADelMetric

xIsisRASNPAAddress.name: xIsisRASNPAAddress
xIsisRASNPAAddress.description: The SNPA Address to which a PDU may be forwarded in order to reach a destination which matches the address prefix of the Reachable Address. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

xIsisRASNPAMask.name: xIsisRASNPAMask
xIsisRASNPAMask.description: A bit mask with 1 bits indicating the positions in the effective destination address from which embedded SNPA information is to be extracted. For the extraction the first octet of the xIsisRASNPAMask object value is aligned with the first octet (AFI) of the NSAP Address. If the xIsisRASNPAMask object value and NSAP Address are of different lengths, the shorter of the two is logically padded with zeros before performing the extraction. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.

xIsisRASNPAPrefix.name: xIsisRASNPAPrefix
xIsisRASNPAPrefix.description: A fixed SNPA prefix for use when the xIsisRAMapType is extractDSP. The SNPA Address to use is formed by concatenating the fixed SNPA prefix with a variable SNPA part that is extracted from the effective destination address. For Reachable Address prefixes in which the entire SNPA is embedded in the DSP the SNPA Prefix shall be null. This object follows the manualOrAutomatic behaviour.
